HEADWORD: Crossbarred
<hw>Cross"barred`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦aum⟧rd`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Secured by, or furnished with, crossbars.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made or patterned in lines crossing each other;
<as>as, <ex>crossbarred</ex> muslin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crossbeak</ent>⟦br⟧
